. Hey all,
I took a thorough look at the code examples tonight. I went ahead and applied the following rules, usually because they were consistent with the rest of the documentation, and in harmony with most formatting guides:
- Braces are followed by indented children on new lines, with the child commas followed by new lines.
- Parentheses, brackets, and all other commas are not followed by new lines or indented children.
- Anonymous functions have one space between the declaration and the opening parenthesis.
- Single-line comments start with two slashes and one space.
- Hexidecimal colors are written uppercase.
- Dissimilar declarations ("different thoughts") are separated by an empty line.
- Markdown JavaScript sections have one empty line outside each of their boundaries, but none touching inside their boundaries.
I've file a pull request:
https://github.com/liferay/alloyui.com/pull/161
By the way, this pull request happens to resolve two related issues:
Unexpected identifier @ http://alloyui.com/examples/datatable/real-world/
CSS 404 @ http://alloyui.com/examples/video/ & http://alloyui.com/examples/video/real-world/
